<title>UPDATE-ATTRIBUTE</title>

</head>
<body>

	<h3><i>I update my attribute to a new value. If this is the first mention of the 

	attribute then I create it.</i> </h3>

	<font size="2" color="gray">Begin micro-behaviour</font>
	<p><b>UPDATE-ATTRIBUTE</b></p>

	<font size="2" color="gray">Begin NetLogo code:</font>
	<pre>substitute-text-area-for columns: 76 attribute-name my-age
substitute-text-area-for columns: 76 rows: 5 attribute-value 42     
substitute-text-area-for columns: 80 rows: 5 comment ; Notes                                                                                      
set attribute-name
    attribute-value
comment</pre>

	<font size="2" color="gray">End NetLogo code</font>
	<h2>Related micro-behaviours</h2>
<p><a href="COPY-ATTRIBUTE.html">COPY-ATTRIBUTE</a> copies the value of an 
attribute from one agent to another. <a href="UPDATE-ATTRIBUTE-REPEATEDLY.html">UPDATE-ATTRIBUTE-REPEATEDLY</a> 
	updates an attribute repeatedly. <a href="DEFINE-PARAMETER.html">DEFINE-PARAMETER</a> creates a model 
parameter (while this micro-behaviour creates one whose value can differ among 
agents).&nbsp; <a href="UPDATE-PARAMETER.html">UPDATE-PARAMETER</a> updates 
parameters.</p>
<h2>Variants</h2>

	<p>Change the attribute name in the first text areas whatever attribute you 
	want to create or set. And second text area can contain any value or an expression that will 
	evaluate to a value.</p>

	<h2>How this works</h2>

	<p>The BehaviourComposer treats specially variables whose name begins with 

	&quot;my-&quot; or &quot;my-next-&quot;. Typically micro-behaviours set the &quot;my-next-&quot; version 

	and read from the &quot;my-&quot;. Whenever the time advances the &quot;my-&quot; variable gets 

	the value of the &quot;my-next-&quot; variable.</p>

	<p>Note that, unlike NetLogo, you don't need to declare &quot;breed&quot; variables.

	</p>

	<h2>History</h2>



	<p><a href="UPDATE-ATTRIBUTE.html">UPDATE-ATTRIBUTE</a> was implemented by Ken Kahn.</p>



